Description: From the trial of St Justin before Rusticus, the prefect
  of Rome
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Death=The Happy Death
By: St Justin
---
The Prefect： ‘Do you suppose that you will ascend into heaven to
receive such a recompense?’

St Justin： ‘I do not suppose it, but I am fully persuaded of it.’
